# b1nix package index — consumed by `bpkg` on b1nix.
# One package per line, fields space-separated. Blank lines and `#` comments ignored.
#
#   name      version  arch     sha256(64-hex of the .tar.gz)                                     url
#
# `arch` is matched against `uname -m` on the target (x86_64 or x86/i686).
# `url` points at the tarball; for jsDelivr use:
#   https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/B1nix/b1nix-pkgs@main/pkgs/<file>.tar.gz
#
# Tarballs are extracted into / on the target, so pack paths relative to root
# (e.g. ./bin/hello, not ./hello). Generated by tools/bpkg-publish.sh in the
# main b1nix repo — do not hand-edit package lines.
#
